The paper proposes a Deep Learning-based approach to domain adaptation, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and software engineering (cs.SD). The paper specifically focuses on sentiment analysis, which is a task commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.SD.
